<span class="openapi-clients-box"><span class="openapi-clients-box-heading">Clients</span><a href="https://docs.apify.com/api/client/python/reference/class/DatasetClientAsync#push_items" target="_blank"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/apify/openapi/b1206ac2adf8f39b05e5a09bf32c2802af58d851/assets/python.svg" class="openapi-clients-box-icon" alt="Apify API Python Client Reference"/></a><a href="https://docs.apify.com/api/client/js/reference/class/DatasetClient#pushItems" target="_blank"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/apify/openapi/b1206ac2adf8f39b05e5a09bf32c2802af58d851/assets/javascript.svg" class="openapi-clients-box-icon" alt="Apify API JavaScript Client Reference" /></a></span><span id="/reference/datasets/item-collection/put-items"></span><span id="/reference/datasets/put-items"></span>Appends an item or an array of items to the end of the dataset.

The POST payload is a JSON object or a JSON array of objects to save into the dataset.


**IMPORTANT:** The limit of request payload size for the dataset is 5 MB. If the array exceeds the size, you'll need to split it into a number of smaller arrays.
